<br>
Renew Elements: Caps out at Level 25, 2HP to 1 Manna heal ratio.<br>
Renew Summoning: Caps out at Level 60, 2.2HP to 1 Manna heal ratio. Not too bad<br>
<br>
Refresh Summoning: Never gets to 2:1 ration unlike the previous two, but has cure disease component. The crippling ratio is not justified by the addition of Cure Disease.<br>
<br>
Transon's Elemental Infusion: Like Renew Summoning, has slightly over 2:1 HP:Manna ratio, but ALSO Cure Disease.<br>
<br>
Now why is it that in 8 levels, our heals can have just drastic changes?<br>
<br>
In my levels between Level 44 and 52, I NEVER came across a disease attacking/slowing mob, although this is due to smart hunting locations. I was also exclusively hunting SeaFurbies in this level period, and they have no disease based abilities.<br>
<br>
However, if you do come across Disease based effects on your pet and you're not grouped with any other class (almost all casting classes get cure disease except Wizards and Enchanters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) then this comes into use. But this isn't my major gripe with this spell...<br>
<br>
Once you get two pet heals, you'll most likely run into a situation where pet health is needed, so you will want to alternate between the two of them due to the large re-cast delays. Once you get Transon's Elemental Infusion and even if you're facing Disease attacking Mobs, you won't want to use Refresh over Renew Summoning. Why? Because the Cure Disease effect is taken care of by Transon's Elemental Infusion which also has a far better HP:Manna ratio than refresh, so you'll most likely be chaining TEI and Renew Summoning, unless the extra 175 HP is so essential that you HAVE to use Refresh and if you get into a situation like that, you're better off Chaining Pets. Even facing off against two Seafurbies and a crippled 49 Fire, Chaining TEI and Renew Summoning was MORE than enough to keep ole flamey alive. In fact, I'm pretty sure I could have got away with just TEI, but probably not only Renew Summoning (I don't have a Manna Conservation III yet, so Renew Summoning pushes ahead in manna efficiency stakes, just)<br>
<br>
Refresh has a massive manna cost for an output that is less than spectacular. With pets costing 200 a pop at this level, there's little use for heals, only those of us who are adamant against chaining seem to keep on using Heals. I never understood why SPECIALISED heals (ala mob specific nukes Undead/Summoned lines) are not more manna efficient than the Priest ones. They always have Players to heal and we always have pets to heal, but we are not given the same efficiency. Post 34, we never even get close to heals near Superiour Healing efficiency, we barely get past Greater Healing efficiency (2:1 ratio, as heavily repeated above)<br>
<br>
I've suggested that our heal line be scrapped and just be clones of the Druid heal like (1, 8, 20, 29, 51, 55, 60. You get the idea) with the same amount healed by with lower manna costs.<br>
<br>
Level 1:<br>
Minor Healing Companoin<br>
Heals 10 HP<br>
Manna: 8<br>
<br>
Level 8:<br>
Lesser Healing Companion<br>
Heals 34 HP<br>
Manna: 20<br>
<br>
Level 20:<br>
Healing Companoin<br>
Heals 100 HP<br>
Manna 50<br>
<br>
Level 29:<br>
Greater Healing Companion<br>
Heals 300 HP<br>
Manna: 110<br>
<br>
Level 51:<br>
Superiour Healing Companion<br>
Heals 575 HP<br>
Manna: 190<br>
<br>
Level 55:<br>
Infuse Companion<br>
Heals 750 HP<br>
Manna: 270<br>
<br>
Level 60:<br>
Companion's Touch<br>
Heals 1000 HP<br>
Manna: 300<br>
<br>
&lt;sketchy numbers, but you know the line it's based on&gt;<br>
<br>
These numbers still make chaining pets more efficient, but the ratios of HP:Manna are far superiour to our current heals.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't really mind so much if the ratio continued at 2/3:1 but they don't get better. <p>Majishia Vie &lt;Wyrd Angles&gt;<br>
